status: MARC21-007: Specific material designation of text
Special class of textual material to which an item belongs.

definition (en): Large print text is oversized print intended for use by the visually impaired.
Braille text is embossed characters that have been formed by raised dots in six-dot cells; braille is intended for use by the visually impaired.
Special material designation of the text is not specified.
Specific material designation other than regular print, large print, braille, text in looseleaf binder.
